rtists','',0),(895,1,'2017-02-03 10:30:46','2017-02-03 10:30:46','','Gaser','','private','closed','closed','','gaser','','','2017-02-28 14:49:40','2017-02-28 14:49:40','',0,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/?post_type=artists&#038;p=895',0,'artists','',0),(896,1,'2017-02-03 10:29:59','2017-02-03 10:29:59','','Dina El Wedidi','','private','closed','closed','','dina-el-wedidi','','','2017-02-28 14:45:35','2017-02-28 14:45:35','',0,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/?post_type=artists&#038;p=896',0,'artists','',0),(897,1,'2017-02-03 10:31:45','2017-02-03 10:31:45','','El Dor El Awal','','private','closed','closed','','el-dor-el-awal','','','2017-02-28 14:46:44','2017-02-28 14:46:44','',0,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/?post_type=artists&#038;p=897',0,'artists','',0),(899,1,'2017-02-03 10:33:11','2017-02-03 10:33:11','Comprising of some of Egypt\'s most talented and original musicians in their own right, it\'s no wonder that electro-pop band Ritza is a much sought-after live show in Cairo. The band\'s upbeat electro-pop sound is infused with robotic vocals in Arabic, electronic beats, synth-based disco grooves and driving bass lines.\r\n','Ritza','','publish','closed','closed','','ritza','','','2017-03-02 12:19:27','2017-03-02 12:19:27','',0,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/?post_type=artists&#038;p=899',0,'artists','',0),(900,1,'2017-02-03 11:37:58','2017-02-03 11:37:58','[vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title=\"About Cairo Jazz Club\" img=\"358\"]Laid back, hi-energy and fun.\n\nFor well over a decade, Cairo Jazz Club LLC has stood the test of time as Cairo’s ultimate live music hub. The vibe achieved in our venue is a lively engaging one where people can enjoy live music, delicious food and bar selections while feeling right at home.\n\nIn the center of it all, the Cairo Jazz Club stage is notoriously established as a portal for manifesting art and expression through music. It has stood witness to the rise of many fresh talents, regularly hosting the finest live acts in town, as well as international artists. We also make it our mission to tirelessly expose new talents and present them with the space and opportunity to grow; starting grounds for countless artists in the independent music scene. Adamant on catering to all tastes while remaining musically objective, Cairo Jazz Club hosts a different event every day, covering various genres in addition to the occasional themed nights.<!--more-->\n\nThe philosophy that has kept us going thus far is simpler than you would think, “We serve good moods” and that is precisely what is on the menu every day of the week. So if you don’t hate having a good time while feeding your appetite with a delectable, diverse menu and euphorically intoxicating cocktails, then Cairo Jazz Club is the place to be.[/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title=\"STAGE HISTORY\" img=\"359\" direction=\"Left\"]\n\nFrom the get go, a fundamental essential to the Cairo Jazz Club experience was its stage, instrumental in the evolution of Cairo’s independent music scene. Cairo Jazz Club has always platformed fresh talent leading to why most of the city’s top end bands such as Wust EL Balad and Screwdriver were born on that stage. Not forgetting the stage till now is a regular host to the finest live acts in town and may acclaimed international artists from all corners of the world. The Club is rightly recognized as the “capital” of live music in the city.\nSome of the many musical talents who have taken to Cairo Jazz Club’s stage:\n\n<strong>Established Egyptian Artists</strong>\n• Fathy Salama\n• Yehya Khalil\n• Rashad Fahim\n• Ahmed Rabie\n• Salah Ragab\n• Ossama Ezz El Din\n<ul>\n 	<li>Hesham Galal</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Internationally Acclaimed Artists</strong>\n• Ilham Madfai\n• Natasha Atlas\n• Stanley Jordan\n• Monica Passos\n• Jay Rodriguez\n\n• Michiel Bortslap\n• Albert Del Rio\n• Mark Alban\n• Last Supper Band\n• Los Banditos Band\n• Ned Kelly\n• Kamal Musallam\n• Mashrou’ Leila\n<ul>\n 	<li>Tania Saleh</li>\n 	<li>Souad Massi</li>\n 	<li>OUM</li>\n 	<li>Ghalia Ben Ali</li>\n 	<li>Zeid Hamdan</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Top Local Artists who debuted @ CJC</strong>\n• Wust EL Balad\n• Beshir\n• The Riff Band\n• Screwdriver\n• Eftekasat\n• Vybe\n• Cocoon\n• Mica\n<ul>\n 	<li>The Big Band Society</li>\n</ul>\n[/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title=\"CJC’s Art\" img=\"361\"]\n\nCairo Jazz Club was very lucky to work with different creative artistic talents over the years. Known for our unique drawings, mystical interior design and authentic print work CJC has to commend the imaginative minds of those who helped inspire our identity and character that followed.\n\n<strong>Amr Qenawi: Current Graphic Designer &amp; Art Director                                                                                              </strong>Although his line of work requires versatility in style, CJC’s resident designer Amr Qenawi’s unique artistic identity is embedded in all aspect of his CJC designs with creative flyers, posters, graphics and interior themed decoration showing admirable objectivity in his work. Qenawi has recently taken on the task of art directing CJC’s themed nights, creating different moods using his creativity and props mostly worked on by his hands.\n\nUpon graduating with a BA in applied arts in 2008, Amr launched his career as a painter and computer graphic artist. He draws inspiration from the likes of surrealist giant, H.R Giger; Spanish Fantasy Characters artist, Luis Royo, and the prince of darkness himself, Marilyn Manson. Amr is also one of the very few artists around that are willing to take on the tedious yet beautifully sophisticated art of Rotoscopy; completing Neobyrd’s entire music video ‘My Sweetheartless’ with a whopping 3800 individually coloured frames within months of filming. <strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FP5ktZWketk\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FP5ktZWketk</a></strong>\n\n<strong>Karine Ghaly:</strong> <strong>CJC Artist responsible for the unique illustrations</strong>\nIf you ever wondered who was the creative mastermind behind the Jazz Club drawings and designs, look no further than artist Karine Ghaly. Born in Alexandria Egypt, Karine graduated from the University of Fine Art Alexandria and went onto attend courses at St Martin’s College of art and design in London. Karine used her love of Egypt and music to help influence the logo and drawings for Cairo Jazz Club. By combining her creative imagination with modern twist she was able to create a feel of freedom and relaxed ambiance matching CJC’s theme. Karine also acknowledges CJC’s owners for having a big impact on the creative process and final designs.\nKarine has had exhibitions at the Ostia Lido’s Art Gallery in Rome. Waterloo’s Art Gallery in Brussels, the Crédit Mutuel in France, Spanish Cultural Center and various locations in Cairo such as International Cultural Center for Cooperation.\n\n<strong>Amr Farouk: Interior Paintings (CJC Agouza) </strong>\nBohemian artist and designer Amr Farouk is the craftsman behind the series of intriguing paintings hung inside Cairo Jazz Club. Amr Farouk was a painter from his early days as a curious child. Born in Cairo, Amr moved to Sinai from the age of 15 and lived a Bedouin lifestyle over the following 22 years. Moving from one area to another, spending a lot of time in the mountains Amr’s artistic talents developed at a rapid rate, excelling him to greater spiritual enlightenment. His travels and free living attitude is very represented in his artworks found at Cairo Jazz Club paintings.\n\n<strong>Mahmoud Fahmy: Graphic Designer  </strong>\nCool and collected Egyptian freelance designer Mahmoud Fathy brought the CJC drawings to life in 2010 and was responsible for the first batch of CJC printed materials including the creative and upbeat series of posters and flyers CJC generated for bands and festivals.\nMahmoud studied design at faculty of Fine Arts in Cairo and work for numerous organizations such as Promo 7 and LOWE Egypt. He currently live in Berlin and works for worldwide advertising agency DDB.<a href=\"http://www.mahmoud-fathy.com/\">http://www.mahmoud-fathy.com/</a>[/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row]','About CJC','','inherit','closed','closed','','57-revision-v1','','','2017-02-03 11:37:58','2017-02-03 11:37:58','',57,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/2017/02/57-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(901,1,'2017-02-03 11:39:30','2017-02-03 11:39:30','[vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title=\"About Cairo Jazz Club\" img=\"358\"]Laid back, hi-energy and fun.\r\n\r\nFor well over a decade, Cairo Jazz Club LLC has stood the test of time as Cairo’s ultimate live music hub. The vibe achieved in our venue is a lively engaging one where people can enjoy live music, delicious food and bar selections while feeling right at home.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nIn the center of it all, the Cairo Jazz Club stage is notoriously established as a portal for manifesting art and expression through music. It has stood witness to the rise of many fresh talents, regularly hosting the finest live acts in town, as well as international artists. We also make it our mission to tirelessly expose new talents and present them with the space and opportunity to grow; starting grounds for countless artists in the independent music scene. Adamant on catering to all tastes while remaining musically objective, Cairo Jazz Club hosts a different event every day, covering various genres in addition to the occasional themed nights.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe philosophy that has kept us going thus far is simpler than you would think, “We serve good moods” and that is precisely what is on the menu every day of the week. So if you don’t hate having a good time while feeding your appetite with a delectable, 