45743_632761290204864_1988096122172937834_n','','','2017-02-13 12:02:07','2017-02-13 12:02:07','',835,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/13445743_632761290204864_1988096122172937834_n.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1863,4,'2017-02-13 12:28:05','2017-02-13 12:28:05','Abou Samra discovered his love of music very early on, and by the age of 13 he had his first pioneer mixer and 2 vinyls. Things snowballed from there and he soon developed himself in the underground scenes of Cairo and Barcelona. Leaving Egypt for two years to pursue his passion for music. Now he\'s back in Egypt to teach the dance scene a thing or two about how tech house and techno done.','Abou Samra','','inherit','closed','closed','','835-autosave-v1','','','2017-02-13 12:28:05','2017-02-13 12:28:05','',835,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/835-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1864,4,'2017-02-22 14:28:07','2017-02-22 14:28:07','Born to an Eritrean Father and Egyptian mother; composer, producer and musician Ahmed Omar was always interested in how African and Oriental cultures could intertwine in music. Ahmed brought musicians with unique African traditional backgrounds together to create a diverse musical dialogue blended with contemporary approcahes  to make the music that became the Africairo project.\n\nto blend of traditional and contemporary approaches.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAfricairo believes that art is the natural way, effective and common among the peoples, to create a dialogue between diverse cultures, customs and traditions, b<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ecause all religions and tribes believe in and practice the language of art. Art here plays an important role to close the distances between communities. So we started from the year 2012 an African music and dance festival in Cairo to meet with each other, to exchange expertise and to search for a common language within Africa.</span>\n\nto think about the relationships between  and began to search out musicians from other traditions\n\n&nbsp;','Ahmed Omar \'Africairo\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','833-autosave-v1','','','2017-02-22 14:28:07','2017-02-22 14:28:07','',833,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/833-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1865,4,'2017-02-13 15:19:43','2017-02-13 15:19:43','Known as the \'Dean of Jazz Musicians\' in Lebanon, Armenian Lebanon-based pianist Arthur Satyan is one of the most important and influential jazz musicians in the region. Professor of Classical Piano at the Lebanese National Conservatory of Music since 1998, he has taught, influenced and inspired many and has p<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">erformed with an array of international stars and jazz giants like Larry Coryell, Charles Davis, Ray Vega, Ed Cherry and Joe Lee Wilson, just to name few.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Arthur Satyan','','inherit','closed','closed','','887-autosave-v1','','','2017-02-13 15:19:43','2017-02-13 15:19:43','',887,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/887-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1867,4,'2017-02-13 15:49:39','2017-02-13 15:49:39','','1237290_10151768523739842_205603963_o','','inherit','closed','closed','','1237290_10151768523739842_205603963_o','','','2017-02-13 15:49:39','2017-02-13 15:49:39','',887,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/1237290_10151768523739842_205603963_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1868,1,'2017-02-14 15:54:12','2017-02-14 15:54:12','Content-Type: text/plain; charset = \"UTF-8\"\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\r\n\r\nHello!\r\n\r\nSent by Postman 1.7.2 - https://wordpress.org/plugins/postman-smtp/\r\n\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\r\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\r\n<head>\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Ty