bsite/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/15542047_10155482220040329_680667178248572178_n.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1968,4,'2017-02-26 15:10:35','2017-02-26 15:10:35','','14064023_1066851863404033_3200924926215321223_n','','inherit','closed','closed','','14064023_1066851863404033_3200924926215321223_n','','','2017-02-26 15:10:35','2017-02-26 15:10:35','',895,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/14064023_1066851863404033_3200924926215321223_n.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1969,7,'2017-02-27 08:55:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','open','','','','','2017-02-27 08:55:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/?p=1969',0,'post','',0),(1970,7,'2017-02-27 08:55:57','2017-02-27 08:55:57','[vc_row][vc_column][cjc_night title=\"Jazz Sunday\" img=\"8\" embed=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?visual=true&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Fusers%2F1819173&amp;show_artwork=true&amp;maxwidth=270&amp;maxheight=150\" color=\"#75252a\"]<span style=\"color: #efc684;\">As the title subtly implies, Cairo Jazz Club started off as Cairo’s core jazz hub before expanding its showcase to a variety of music genres. CJC’s signature Jazz night plays refuge to genuine music enthusiasts, platforming the best of jazz and world fusion, performed by Egypt’s most sophisticated International and local musicians. </span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #efc684;\">Some of our X Sunday regulars; Cocoon, Voice &amp; Bass, Hassan Ramzy and H.O.H.</span>\n\n[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Manic Monday\" img=\"907\" embed=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ds4blep9EQE\" color=\"#50223c\"]Manic Monday offers cool and current dance beats for our energetic and adventurous music devotees. This night is always trending, always slick and always ready to satisfy.\n\nSome of our Manic Monday regulars; Ouzo, Gawdat, Aly Goede and Aguizi &amp; Fahim.[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Alt Tuesday\" img=\"910\" embed=\"https://soundcloud.com/cairo-jazz-club/mem-machine-eat-man-at-cairo-jazz-club-jan-2017\" color=\"#322e3d\"]Alt Tuesday provides originality and uniqueness in the form of live bands, electronic musicians and acoustic artists. If you are looking for musical diversity week after week, this is your night.\n\nSome of our Alt Tuesday regulars; Radio Acid, Dokkan, The Meteors Project and Wust El Balad. [/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Spinning Wednesday\" img=\"911\" embed=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ds4blep9EQE\" color=\"#971f20\"]Home to our famous ‘Boogie Night’, Spinning Wednesday adds a dose of fun and nostalgia to the midweek. This signature party night reminds us that, whatever age we are, it’s always good to let our hair down.\n\nSome of our Spinning Wednesday regulars; Ramy DJunkie, Feedo, A.K and Disco Masr.\n\n<p class=\"\">Boogie Night (Boogie / Disco)                Say Whaat!? (RnB &amp; Hip Hop)\nDisco 7amra (Arabic Electro Disco)        Old Skool House (90’s House)\nDirrrty Pop! (90’s Pop)                             Bigger Better Louder (RnB &amp; Hip Hop)\nTaxi El Sahra (Arabic Pop)\n\n[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Thursday Night Live\" img=\"914\" color=\"#e4722c\"]Thursday Night Live events kick start every weekend with a lineup of our most vibrant and energetic bands and electronic acts; performing the hits we all love to hear, from fun covers, and rockin’ originals to hearty dancefloor beats.\n\nSome of our Thursday Night Live regulars; Massar Egbari, Ritza, Funk Off and Glass Onion.\n\n[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Friday Fever\" img=\"916\" color=\"#414141\"]House music with a dynamic twist is on offer every Friday Fever, making CJC a no-brainer weekend dance haven party choice. Leave all inhibitions at the door and come ready to dance.\n\nSome of our Friday Fever regulars; Mohasseb, A- Squared, Misty &amp; Hafez and Special K.[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Saturday L\'oriental\" img=\"918\" embed=\"https://soundcloud.com/cairo-jazz-club/asia-madani\" color=\"#5c5237\"]Saturday L’oriental musicians add a dash of tradition and a sprinkle of mystery with great musicianship to awaken authentic and contemporary Arabian flare in all of us.\n\nSome of our Saturday L\'oriental regulars; Basheer, El Dor El Awal, Sorour and Hawas. [/cjc_night][/vc_column][/vc_row]','CJC Nights','','inherit','closed','closed','','65-revision-v1','','','2017-02-27 08:55:57','2017-02-27 08:55:57','',65,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/65-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1971,2,'2017-02-27 10:05:40','2017-02-27 10:05:40','[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text][metaslider id=1777][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][cjc_parallax_slider title=\"UPCOMING EVENTS\" id=\"bubble\"][cjc-parallax-event-circles][/cjc_parallax_slider][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column el_class=\"photogallery\"][ess_grid alias=\"featured gallery\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','338-revision-v1','','','2017-02-27 10:05:40','2017-02-27 10:05:40','',338,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/338-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1972,4,'2017-02-27 11:28:31','2017-02-27 11:28:31','{\n    \"Cairo-Jazz-Club::cjc-identity-email\": {\n        \"value\": \"info@cairojazzclub.com\",\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 4\n    }\n}','','','trash','closed','closed','','e6da7299-1010-4d1d-b1bf-cbd7dbfad986','','','2017-02-27 11:28:31','2017-02-27 11:28:31','',0,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/e6da7299-1010-4d1d-b1bf-cbd7dbfad986/',0,'customize_changeset','',0),(1973,4,'2017-02-27 11:38:37','2017-02-27 11:38:37','[vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title=\"About Cairo Jazz Club\" img=\"358\"]Laid back, hi-energy and fun.\r\n\r\nFor well over a decade, Cairo Jazz Club has stood the test of time as Cairo’s ultimate live music hub. The vibe achieved in our venue is a lively and engaging one where people can enjoy live music, delicious food and bar selections, while feeling right at home. In the center of it all, the Cairo Jazz Club stage is notoriously established as a portal for manifesting art and expression through music. It stands witness to the rise of many fresh talents, regularly hosting the finest live acts in town, as well as exciting international artists. We also make it our mission to tirelessly expose new talent and present them with the space and opportunity to grow; we are the starting ground for countless artists in the independent music scene. Adamant on catering to all tastes while remaining musically objective, Cairo Jazz Club hosts a different event every day, covering various genres, in addition to the occasional themed nights.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nThe philosophy that has kept us going thus far is simpler than you would think, “We serve good moods”. And that is precisely what is on the menu every day of the week. So if you enjoy having a good time while feeding your appetite with a delectable, diverse menu and euphorically intoxicating cocktails, then Cairo Jazz Club is the place to be.[/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][cjc_about_section title=\"STAGE HISTORY\" img=\"359\" direction=\"Left\"]From the get go, a fundamental essential to the Cairo Jazz Club experience was its stage, instrumental in the evolution of Cairo’s independent music scene. Cairo Jazz Club has always platformed fresh talent leading to why most of the city’s top end bands such as <a href=\"http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/artists/\">Wust El Balad</a> and Screwdriver were born on that stage. The stage until now is a regular host to the finest live acts in town and. The Club is rightly recognized as the “capital” of live music in the city.\r\nSome of the many musical talents who have taken to Cairo Jazz Club’s stage:\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<strong>Established Egyptian Artists / Bands</strong>\r\nFathy Salama\r\nYehya Khalil\r\nRashad Fahim\r\nAhmed Rabie\r\nSalah Ragab\r\n\r\nH