\n<strong>Amr Qenawi: Current Graphic Designer &amp; Art Director                                                                                       </strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough his line of work requires versatility in style, CJC’s resident designer Amr Qenawi’s unique artistic identity is embedded in all aspect of his CJC designs. Creative flyers, posters, graphics and interior themed decoration all show the admirable objectivity in his work. Qenawi has recently taken on the task of art directing CJC’s themed nights, creating different moods using his creativity and props mostly worked on by hand.\r\n\r\nUpon graduating with a BA in applied arts in 2008, Amr launched his career as a painter and computer graphic artist. He draws inspiration from the likes of surrealist giant, H.R Giger; Spanish Fantasy Characters artist, Luis Royo; and the prince of darkness himself, Marilyn Manson. Amr is also one of the very few artists around that are willing to take on the tedious yet beautifully sophisticated art of Rotoscopy, completing Neobyrd’s entire music video ‘<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FP5ktZWketk\" target=\"_blank\">My Sweetheartless</a>’ with a whopping 3800 individually coloured frames within months of filming.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Karine Ghaly:</strong> <strong>CJC Artist responsible for the unique illustrations</strong>\r\nIf you ever wondered who was the creative mastermind behind the illustrations that inspired everything from our logo to our tables and façade, look no further than artist Karine Ghaly. Born in Alexandria Egypt, Karine graduated from the University of Fine Art Alexandria and went on to attend courses at St Martin’s College of art and design in London. Karine used her love of Egypt and of music to help influence the logo and illustrations for Cairo Jazz Club. By combining her creative imagination with a modern twist she was able to create a feel of freedom and relaxed environment matching CJC’s ambiance. Karine also acknowledges CJC’s owners for having a big impact on the creative process and final designs.\r\nKarine has had exhibitions at the Ostia Lido’s Art Gallery in Rome. Waterloo’s Art Gallery in Brussels, the Crédit Mutuel in France, Spanish Cultural Center, and various locations in Cairo such as International Cultural Center for Cooperation.\r\n\r\n<strong>Amr Farouk: Interior Paintings (CJC Agouza) </strong>\r\nBohemian artist and designer Amr Farouk is the craftsman behind the series of intriguing paintings hanging inside Cairo Jazz Club. Amr Farouk was a painter from his early days as a curious child. Born in Cairo, Amr moved to Sinai from the age of 15 and lived a Bedouin lifestyle over the following 22 years. Moving from one area to another, spending a lot of time in the mountains, Amr’s artistic talents developed at a rapid rate, excelling him to greater spiritual enlightenment. His travels and free living attitude is well represented in his art at Cairo Jazz Club.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mahmoud Fahmy: Graphic Designer  </strong>\r\nCool and collected Egyptian freelance designer Mahmoud Fathy brought the CJC drawings to life in 2010 and was responsible for the first batch of CJC printed materials including the creative and upbeat series of posters and flyers CJC generated for bands and festivals. Mahmoud studied design at faculty of Fine Arts in Cairo and worked for numerous organizations such as Promo 7 and LOWE Egypt. He currently lives in Berlin and works for worldwide advertising agency DDB. [/cjc_about_section][/vc_column][/vc_row]','About CJC','','inherit','closed','closed','','57-revision-v1','','','2017-02-27 11:50:57','2017-02-27 11:50:57','',57,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/57-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1981,4,'2017-02-27 12:02:48','2017-02-27 12:02:48','[vc_row][vc_column][cjc_night title=\"Jazz Sunday\" img=\"8\" embed=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?visual=true&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Fusers%2F1819173&amp;show_artwork=true&amp;maxwidth=270&amp;maxheight=150\" color=\"#75252a\"]<span style=\"color: #efc684;\">As the title subtly implies, Cairo Jazz Club started off as Cairo’s core jazz hub before expanding its showcase to a variety of music genres. CJC’s signature Jazz night plays refuge to genuine music enthusiasts, platforming the best of jazz and world fusion, performed by Egypt’s most sophisticated International and local musicians. </span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #efc684;\">Some of our X Sunday regulars; Cocoon, Voice &amp; Bass, Hassan Ramzy and H.O.H.</span>\n\n[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Manic Monday\" img=\"907\" embed=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ds4blep9EQE\" color=\"#50223c\"]Manic Monday offers cool and current dance beats for our energetic and adventurous music devotees. This night is always trending, always slick and always ready to satisfy.\n\nSome of our Manic Monday regulars; Ouzo, Gawdat, Aly Goede and Aguizi &amp; Fahim.[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Alt Tuesday\" img=\"910\" embed=\"https://soundcloud.com/cairo-jazz-club/mem-machine-eat-man-at-cairo-jazz-club-jan-2017\" color=\"#322e3d\"]Alt Tuesday provides originality and uniqueness in the form of live bands, electronic musicians and acoustic artists. If you are looking for musical diversity week after week, this is your night.\n\nSome of our Alt Tuesday regulars; Radio Acid, Dokkan, The Meteors Project and Wust El Balad. [/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Spinning Wednesday\" img=\"911\" embed=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ywFqy56NLuI\" color=\"#971f20\"]Home to our famous ‘Boogie Night’, Spinning Wednesday adds a dose of fun and nostalgia to the midweek. This signature party night reminds us that, whatever age we are, it’s always good to let our hair down.\n\nSome of our Spinning Wednesday regulars; Ramy DJunkie, Feedo, A.K and Disco Masr.\n\n<p class=\"\">Boogie Night (Boogie / Disco)                Say Whaat!? (RnB &amp; Hip Hop)\nDisco 7amra (Arabic Electro Disco)        Old Skool House (90’s House)\nDirrrty Pop! (90’s Pop)                             Bigger Better Louder (RnB &amp; Hip Hop)\nTaxi El Sahra (Arabic Pop)\n\n[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Thursday Night Live\" img=\"914\" color=\"#e4722c\"]Thursday Night Live events kick start every weekend with a lineup of our most vibrant and energetic bands and electronic acts; performing the hits we all love to hear, from fun covers, and rockin’ originals to hearty dancefloor beats.\n\nSome of our Thursday Night Live regulars; Massar Egbari, Ritza, Funk Off and Glass Onion.\n\n[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Friday Fever\" img=\"916\" embed=\"https://soundcloud.com/cairo-jazz-club/mohasseb\" color=\"#414141\"]House music with a dynamic twist is on offer every Friday Fever, making CJC a no-brainer weekend dance haven party choice. Leave all inhibitions at the door and come ready to dance.\n\nSome of our Friday Fever regulars; Mohasseb, A- Squared, Misty &amp; Hafez and Special K.[/cjc_night][cjc_night title=\"Saturday L\'oriental\" img=\"918\" embed=\"https://soundcloud.com/cairo-jazz-club/asia-madani\" color=\"#5c5237\"]Saturday L’oriental musicians add a dash of tradition and a sprinkle of mystery with great musicianship to awaken authentic and contemporary Arabian flare in all of us.\n\nSome of our Saturday L\'oriental regulars; Basheer, El Dor El Awal, Sorour and Hawas. [/cjc_night][/vc_column][/vc_row]','CJC Nights','','inherit','closed','closed','','65-revision-v1','','','2017-02-27 12:02:48','2017-02-27 12:02:48','',65,'http://104.40.211.237/Cairo-Jazz-Club.wp/website/65-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1982,4,'2017-02-27 12:14:11','2017-02-27 12:14:11','[vc_row][vc_column][cjc_night title=\"Jazz Sunday\" img=\"8\" color=\"#75252a\"]<span style=\"color: #efc684;\">As the title subtly implies, Cairo Jazz Club started off as Cairo’s core jazz hub before expanding its showcase to a variety of music genres. CJC’s signature Jazz night plays refuge to genuine music enthusiasts, platforming the best of ja